<2ND_LINE>PM-Stolen Baby,0209</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Newborn Kidnapped From Hospital Found Healthy A Week Later</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GRASSE, France (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 9-day-old baby taken from his mother's
hospital room last week has been found in the home of a woman
depressed following a recent miscarriage , police said.
   Ali Salah appeared to be in perfect health when he was found
Tuesday, polce said.
   Daniele Imbert, 43, and her common-law husband identified only
as Mr. Lazur were being held for questioning but were not
immediately charged.
   Police sources, speaking on condition of anonymity, said she at
first claimed the boy was her own, but under questioning admitted
she had taken him from his mother's hospital room, three days after
his birth.
   The mother, Latifa Salah, reported that Ali disappeared last
Wednesday from his cradle in her room in the maternity ward at the
Grasse hospital while she was taking a shower.
   Witnesses reported seeing a woman who appeared to be in her 40s
carrying a baby out of the hospital at about that time, and police
distributed a composite sketch. Neighbors of Daniele Imbert spotted
the resemblance and alerted authorities.
   Police sources said the woman in custody had a miscarriage in
June, and wanted a child desperately.
