<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is the 272-152 roll call Tuesday by which
the House fell short of the two-thirds majority vote needed to
override President Reagan's veto of proposed new curbs on textile,
apparel and shoe imports.
   A ``yes'' vote is a vote to override the veto.
   Voting yes, shown here as Y, were 203 Democrats and 69
Republicans.
   Voting no, shown here as N, were 47 Democrats and 105
Republicans.
   X denotes those not voting.
   Present denotes those who voted they were ``present'' at the
time of the vote but did not vote ``yes'' or ``no'' on the issue.
   There are three vacancies in the 435-seat House.
</TEXT>
