<1ST_LINE>r p PM-Debate-Glance     10-05 0109</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Debate-Glance,100</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Vice Presidential Debate at a Glance</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here at a glance are facts on tonight's vice
presidential debate:
   WHO _ Sens. Lloyd Bentsen, D-Texas, and Dan Quayle, R-Ind.
   WHERE _ Omaha, Neb.
   WHEN _ 8:30 p.m. to 10 p.m. EDT.
   FORMAT _ Quayle has two minutes to answer first question,
Bentsen has one minute to rebut; then they reverse for next
question and so on until final statements.
   QUESTIONERS _ Moderator: Judy Woodruff of public broadcasting's
MacNeil@Lehrer NewsHour. Panel: Tom Brokaw of NBC, Jon Margolis of
the Chicago Tribune and Britt Hume of ABC News.
   TV _ Live coverage by all major networks.
</TEXT>
