<HEAD>Upper Midwest Gets Wintry Chill</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   A blast of cold wind whipped through the upper Midwest today,
bringing frost and freezing temperatures to parts of Michigan,
Wisconsin, Illinois, Indiana, Missouri, Iowa, Minnesota, Nebraska
and Kansas.
   Midnight temperatures were in the 30s and 40s across the Great
Lakes, freezing from northwest Wisconsin and the upper Mississippi
Valley into the Dakotas, and in the 40s and 50s across Idaho.
   Scattered rain continued into the early morning from southern
New England to the lower Great Lakes, from western Nebraska to
eastern Colorado and northeast New Mexico, and along the northern
Pacific Coast. Showers and a few thunderstorms were scattered over
Florida.
   Today's forecast called for showers from northern New England to
the lower Great Lakes.
   Temperatures were predicted to be unseasonably low from the
Plains to the northern half of the Atlantic Coast; in the 40s in
northern Maine and the Great Lakes; in the 50s and 60s from
southern Maine to North Carolina through the Ohio Valley and the
Tennessee Valley, from northern South Carolina to northern
Mississippi, from Arkansas to Minnesota, from the Dakotas to
northern Texas, from eastern Colorado to the upper Missouri Valley
and the northern Pacific Coast; in the 80s in Florida, southern
Texas and Nevada; in the 90s to near 105 degrees through the desert
Southwest; and in the 70s throughout the rest of the nation.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 22
degrees at Hibbing, Minn., to 86 degrees at Blythe, Calif.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 51 fair; Boston 48 drizzle; Buffalo 43 fair;
Charleston, S.C. 58 fair; Cincinnati 39 fair; Cleveland 43 showers;
Detroit 43 cloudy; Miami 75 partly cloudy; New York 53 partly
cloudy; Philadelphia 49 fair; Pittsburgh 38 fair; Portland, Maine
43 showers; Washington 55 fog.
   _Central: Bismarck 23 fair; Chicago 41 windy; Dallas-Fort Worth
55 fair; Denver 39 partly cloudy; Des Moines 34 fair; Indianapolis
41 fair; Kansas City 39 partly cloudy; Minneapolis-St. Paul 33
fair; Nashville 43 fair; New Orleans 66 fair; St. Louis 42 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 62 cloudy; Anchorage 41 rain; Las Vegas 75
fair; Los Angeles 62 fog; Phoenix 83 fair; Salt Lake City 56 fair;
San Diego 63 cloudy; San Francisco 58 fair; Seattle 57 fog.
   _Canada: Montreal 45 cloudy; Toronto 36 fog.
