went in, did their thing and got out.''
   Among the leads police are checking is a failed real estate
deal, involving a downtown Los Angeles building, that forced Luby
and his estranged wife, Sandra, into bankruptcy.
   Luby, a former American Express executive, told police the
attackers asked him if he was Roger Luby, Armstrong said. Then,
they pistol-whipped the two and cut Luby's ankle, knicking his
Achilles tendon.
   ``The way the attack went down, it looks like she (Wayne) was in
the wrong place at the wrong time,'' Jackson said. ``It was meant
as a message to him.''
   Ms. Wayne said Tuesday that one of the attackers said: ``You're
messing with the wrong guy. Next time, we'll kill you.''
   Luby and Ms. Wayne, whose hands and feet were bound behind them,
were found by Luby's houseboy, who freed them and called police.
They were treated at Hoag Memorial Hospital and released.
