southern Tanzania and destroyed 39 homes and left 173 people
homeless, Radio Tanzania reported Wednesday.
   The broadcast, monitored in Nairobi, reported no deaths or
injuries in the fire Sunday at Chawa village in the southeastern
Mtwara region. Officials there said the village was surrounded by
high grass and that the area had not had rain since July.
