<HEAD>North Korea Says South Fired At Guard Post In DMZ</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   North Korea accused South Korean troops Wednesday
of firing at one of the North's guard posts in the demilitarized
zone separating the countries.
   The North also accused the South of deliberately increasing
tensions after the Olympic Games.
   The North's official Korean Central News Agency said the ``grave
military provocation'' occurred in the eastern portion of the DMZ
at about 1:20 p.m.
   ``Today they fired several pinpoint shots at our side's post
from an artillery piece which they had carried into the DMZ by
stealth,'' said the English-language report monitored in Toyko.
