<HEAD>Minor Explosion Damages Helicopter in Presidential Fleet</HEAD>
<DATELINE>QUANTICO, Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A minor fuel explosion damaged one of the
Marine Corps HMX-1 helicopters used to transport President Reagan.
   The explosion occurred Tuesday in a hangar at the Marine base
here while a soldier tested a newly replaced fuel pump, Gunnery
Sgt. Dean Chamberlain said.
   Sgt. Adam W. Shelburg suffered a broken leg, Chamberlain said.
   The explosion caused a small fire that was extinguished before
it could spread to the other helicopter in the hangar, Chamberlain
said.
   The military and engineers from Sikorsky, the helicopter
manufacturer, will investigate.
   Chamberlain said the base uses several helicopters to transport
the president and does not anticipate any reduction of service
because of the explosion.
