<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Freak Shooting,0151</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Shot Through Apartment Floor Kills Man Below</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AUSTIN, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man living in an apartment complex killed
his downstairs neighbor Wednesday by accidentally firing a pistol
through the floor, police said. The victim was shot in the chest
while lying in bed.
   William Howard Tate, 43, fired his .45-caliber automatic without
realizing it was loaded, police said.
   ``It's like the old saying that more people have been killed
with unloaded guns than with loaded guns,'' said Sgt. Will
Beechinor.
   Beechinor said Tate was showing the weapon to his wife the night
before. When he awoke in the morning, he noticed the gun was
half-cocked.
   He pulled the hammer back to let it down and the gun fired,
Beechinor said.
   The shooting was ruled accidental by the Travis County medical
examiner, Beechinor said.
   The victim's identity was not immediately released.
