<1ST_LINE>u w AM-BRF--EBStrike     10-05 0183</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--EB Strike,180</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Union, Electric Boat Officials Negotiate At Federal Mediation
Agency</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Union negotiators and officials representing
the Electric Boat Division of General Dynamics Corp. met with
federal mediators for eight hours Wednesday to try to settle a
3-month-old strike at the company's main shipyard in Groton, Conn.,
that has crippled the submarine maker.
   Negotiating teams for the Metal Trades Council and the company
met behind closed doors at the Federal Mediation and Conciliation
Service before breaking up at 9:15 p.m. without announcing a
resolution.
   The bargaining session was scheduled to resume Thursday morning.
   Officials refused to discuss or characterize Wednesday's talks,
saying representatives for both sides said they were asked by the
federal agency not to discuss the negotiations. .
   ``I can't make any comment on whether we're optimistic or
pessimistic. We're just going to meet tomorrow and see what
happens,'' said mediator Thomas Carroll.
   Wednesday's meeting was the first major bargaining session since
both sides broke off talks after meeting Aug. 11 and 12 with the
federal agency. Union officials requested the new round of talks.
</TEXT>
