<HEAD>European Community Opens China Delegation</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The 12-nation Commission of European Communities
formally opened a permanent delegation to China, the organization's
external relations commissioner said Wednesday.
   The delegation, headed by Ambassador Pierre Duchateau, will
promote economic cooperation and trade between China and the EC as
well as coordinate efforts between its 12 member nations, Willy De
Clercq told a news conference.
   The commission is the central body of the European Economic
Community, which is China's top supplier of high technology and
third largest trading partner after Hong Kong and Japan. Trade
between China and the community totaled $12.44 billion in 1987, De
Clercq said.
