<HEAD>Grandson Of Coleman Co. Founder Elected Board Chairman</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WICHITA, Kan. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sheldon C. Coleman, grandson of the Coleman
Company Inc.'s founder, has been elected company board chairman.
   The younger Coleman succeeds his father, Sheldon Coleman, who
died Sept. 21 at age 86.
   Coleman, the 88-year-old company's third chairman, also is
president and chief executive officer. Founder W.C. Coleman was
chairman until his death in 1957.
   Coleman, 35, first worked for the company in factory production
jobs during high school and college. He served in various posts
before becoming vice president and general manager of Coleman's
largest division, Group One, in 1984. He was named president last
year. His election to the chairmanship was announced Tuesday.
   Coleman has a bachelor's degree from the University of Kansas
and a master's from California State University-Fullerton.
   The Coleman Co., with approximately $265 million in assets,
manufactures outdoor recreation equipment and home heating and air
conditioning products.
