<1ST_LINE>r f BC-AutoRecall     10-05 0100</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Auto Recall,0105</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>VW Recalls 1,700 Late 1988 Jettas</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TROY, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Volkswagen United States on Wednesday said it
was recalling about 1,700 late-1988 model Jetta cars to inspect and
replace, if necessary, a brake vacuum unit.
   Volkswagen said it was possible the unit could separate during
heavy braking, which would, in turn, diminish braking power.
   The company said in a news release it was aware of no accidents
or injuries due to the problem.
   Owners of the vehicles are being notified by mail. Inspection
and replacement of the unit, if necessary, would be free to the
consumer.
</TEXT>
